==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
From Old (and modern) French [[glu]] (now ‘birdlime’), from late Latin [[glus|glus, glut-]], from Latin [[gluten#Latin|gluten]].

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ɡluː/}}
*{{SAMPA|/glu:/}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-uː|-uː]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A hard gelatin made by boiling bones and hides, used in solution as an [[adhesive]]; or any sticky adhesive substance.
# ''(obsolete)'' [[birdlime|Birdlime]].

